    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="kal_ch.00005_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place" rend="right">Esopus N.Y.</name>
                    <date when="1876-04-04" rend="right">April 4, 1876</date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Dear Walt:</salute>
            </opener>

            <p>I wrote a letter to the Tribune the other day touching you &amp; your matters &amp;
                if they publish it I wish you would send me the paper as I do not see the daily
                except I am away from home. I saw their editorial of Tuesday &amp; was much
                incensed by it. I presume it is Bayard Taylor's <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="kal_ch.00006_large.jpg" type="verso"/>hand.<ptr target="n1063"/></p>

            <p>I am on the sick list now from quinsy <choice><orig>soar</orig><reg>sore</reg></choice> throat &amp; am very distressed. I wish you would
                drop me a line. I wrote to you a week or two ago.</p>

            <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately</salute>
                <signed rend="right">John Burroughs</signed>
            </closer>
        </body>
    </text>
